        "comment": {
            "comments": [
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13409523/comment/17445933",
                    "id": "17445933",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thisisnic",
                        "name": "thisisnic",
                        "key": "thisisnic",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=39937",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=39937",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=39937",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=39937"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Nicola Crane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Africa/Casablanca"
                    },
                    "body": "I was in a discussion about this where it was suggested that this potentially could be set up by only installing the packages in {{Depends}}, and not {{Suggests}}, but from looking this up online, I think this can be run via, e.g. {{_R_CHECK_DEPENDS_ONLY_=true  R CMD check arrow_5.0.0.9000.tar.gz}}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thisisnic",
                        "name": "thisisnic",
                        "key": "thisisnic",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=39937",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=39937",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=39937",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=39937"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Nicola Crane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Africa/Casablanca"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-11-18T13:45:46.808+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-11-18T13:45:46.808+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13409523/comment/17446045",
                    "id": "17446045",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jonkeane",
                        "name": "jonkeane",
                        "key": "jonkeane",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34057",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34057",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34057",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34057"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Keane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "I might be mistaken, but I believe  that {{_R_CHECK_DEPENDS_ONLY_=true}} makes it so that {{R CMD CHECK}} doesn't proactively error if a package listed in suggests is not available.\r\n\r\nThe CI proposed is (kind of) the flipside of that (though will require using that flag, I believe): run the checks and _make sure_ that the suggested packages are definitely not installed/available.  ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jonkeane",
                        "name": "jonkeane",
                        "key": "jonkeane",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34057",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34057",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34057",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34057"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Keane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "created": "2021-11-18T17:00:10.576+0000",
                    "updated": "2021-11-18T17:00:10.576+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13409523/comment/17447846",
                    "id": "17447846",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thisisnic",
                        "name": "thisisnic",
                        "key": "thisisnic",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=39937",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=39937",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=39937",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=39937"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Nicola Crane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Africa/Casablanca"
                    },
                    "body": "I had a bit of a check of this in R Internals (https://cran.r-project.org/doc/manuals/r-devel/R-ints.html) and there's this exerpt:\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n_R_CHECK_SUGGESTS_ONLY_ : If set to a true value, running examples, tests and vignettes is done with a temporary library directory populated by all the Depends/Imports/Suggests packages. (As exceptions, packages in a \u2018VignetteBuilder\u2019 field are always made available.) Default: false (but true for CRAN submission checks: some of the regular checks use true and some use false).\r\n\r\n_R_CHECK_DEPENDS_ONLY_: As for _R_CHECK_SUGGESTS_ONLY_ but using only Depends/Imports (and the exceptions, including test-suite managers in \u2018Suggests\u2019). Default: false\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nIn addition, the description in the README linked to above says \"tests on x86_64 Linux with R-devel using _R_CHECK_DEPENDS_ONLY_=true, so packages in Suggests (and Enhances) are not available, (other than recommended packages).\"\r\n\r\nMy interpretation of this would be that it is just that flag that is required.  However, if you suspect anything more complicated than expected is going on (as I know can be the case with these kinds of things), I'm happy to do a more thorough job of setting this up manually anyway - let me know what you think [~jonkeane].\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thisisnic",
                        "name": "thisisnic",
                        "key": "thisisnic",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=39937",
